  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH basic service delivery at Juba IDP sites, South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is intended to improve access to safe water among the target community and ensuring proper hygiene and sanitation related behaviour and practice of the Internally Displaced Persons (IDP) community targeted. The key activities implemented under this project are construction/repair/maintenance of water kiosks and networks, training of kiosk attendants, sensitization of people for safe sanitation practices, repair/rehabilitation of latrine blocks, repair/rehabilitation of bathing shelter, rehabilitation/maintenance of solid waste facilities, messaging the target community hygiene information.</narrative>
  </description>
